headline: Domino’s Pizza price target raised to $515 from $475 at TD Cowen
summary: TD Cowen raised the firm’s price target on Domino’s Pizza (DPZ) to $515 from $475 and keeps a Buy rating on the shares. The firm met with management and came away more bullish on the 2025 story. They remain encouraged by the multi-pronged Hungry for More strategic plan that prompts them to model 2025E U.S. same store sales rabove guidance. headline: 3 Reasons Why Domino's Pizza Stock Could Be a Great Buy for Investors Who Think Like Warren Buffett
summary: On any given morning in Omaha, Nebraska, one can expect to find Warren Buffett buying breakfast at the local McDonald's. The billionaire investor loves to stop by the hamburger chain on his way to the office to run his trillion-dollar empire Berkshire Hathaway.  On Nov. 14, Berkshire Hathaway disclosed that it had purchased nearly 1.3 million shares of Domino's Pizza.  At 94 years old, he's started entrusting more investment decisions to certain people around him.
